54-SKY130RTL D5SK5 L2 â†’ Lab: For & For Generate (Part 2)
ğŸ”¹ Why for is preferred over case

Scalability â†’ for easily handles large bit-widths (e.g., 128-bit bus), while case becomes too long.

Parameterization â†’ works smoothly with parameters/generics for flexible designs.

Compact Code â†’ avoids repetitive code that case would require.

Less Error-Prone â†’ no risk of missing cases (which can infer latches).

Synthesis Friendly â†’ tools unroll for into equivalent hardware automatically.

